hound /haʊnd/

(hounding,hounded,hounds) 

1. N-COUNT A hound is a type of dog that is often used for hunting or racing. 猎犬; 赛犬 

例： Rainey's chief interest in life is hunting with hounds. 雷尼一生中的主要嗜好是带着猎犬去打猎。 

2. N-COUNT ( in combination ) 结合词 

例： an otterhound 

例： a deerhound 

3. N-COUNT either of a pair of horizontal bars that reinforce the running gear of a horse-drawn vehicle 马车两边的固定横杆 

4. V-T If someone hounds you, they constantly disturb or speak to you in an annoying or upsetting way. (不断地) 烦扰 

例： Newcomers are constantly hounding them for advice. 新来的人老是缠着他们问这问那的。 

5. V-T If someone is hounded out of a job or place, they are forced to leave it, often because other people are constantly criticizing them. 迫使 (某人) 离开 [usu passive] 

例： There is a general view around that he has been hounded out of office by the press. 人们普遍认为是媒体迫使他离职的。

</div>

